Police command in Zamfara says it has succeeded in the rescue of one Abdulrahman Abubakar, who was kidnapped in Kebbi State after spending three days in captivity. The command’s spokesperson, SP Muhammad Shehu made the disclosure in a statement issued on Sunday in Gusau. “On Feb. 10, the command’s tactical operatives on confidence building/rescue mission operation along Tsafe – Kucheri – Yankara Federal High Way succeeded in the rescue of a 20 year old Abdulrahman Abubakar, a native of Gwandu emirate in Kebbi state. “The rescue of the victim was part of the command’s ongoing effort to stem the tide of kidnapping and other related crime in the state. “The victim informed the police that he was abducted in Gwandu town, Kebbi state by unidentified persons on motorcycle,” Shehu said (NAN)